#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code har subarray ka range directly nikalne ke bajay,
total contribution of maximums - total contribution of minimums karta hai.

1. Pehle sumSubarrayMins() se total sum of all subarray minimums nikala gaya hai.
2. Phir sumSubarrayMaxs() se total sum of all subarray maximums nikala gaya hai.
3. Final answer:
   total maximum contribution - total minimum contribution

Kaise contribution nikal rahe hain:
1. Har element ke liye find karte hain:
   - minimum case me: PSE aur NSE
   - maximum case me: PGE aur NGE
2. Inse pata chalta hai ki current element kitne subarrays me min/max banega.
3. Formula:
   contribution = arr[i] * leftChoices * rightChoices

Main idea:
Har subarray generate nahi kar rahe.
Bas count kar rahe hain ki koi element minimum kitni baar ban raha hai
aur maximum kitni baar ban raha hai.

Important edge point:
Duplicates handle karne ke liye min aur max dono cases me
strict aur non-strict comparisons carefully use kiye gaye hain,
taaki double counting na ho.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {
    private long sumSubarrayMins(int[] arr) {

        int[] pse = findPse(arr);
        int[] nse = findNse(arr);
        long total = 0;
        int mod = (int)(1e9 + 7);

        for(int i=0; i<arr.length; i++){
            int left = i - pse[i];
            int right = nse[i] - i;
            total += 1L * left * right * arr[i];
        }

        return total;
    }

    private int[] findNse(int[] arr){
        Deque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        int n = arr.length;
        int[] nse = new int[n];

        for(int i=n-1; i>=0; i--){
            while(!stack.isEmpty() && arr[stack.peek()] >= arr[i]){
                stack.pop();
            }

            nse[i] = stack.isEmpty() ? n : stack.peek();
            stack.push(i);
        }
        return nse;
    }

    private int[] findPse(int[] arr){
        Deque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        int n = arr.length;
        int[] pse = new int[n];

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            //Why there is no = sign in while condition ?
            // Because of an edge case where elements are same say 1,1. In this case
            // the 1st index element 1 will duplicate a subarray that has already been calculated as a result 
            // to eliminate this edge case, we didn't use = sign
            while(!stack.isEmpty() && arr[stack.peek()] > arr[i]){
                stack.pop();
            }

            pse[i] = stack.isEmpty() ? -1 : stack.peek();
            stack.push(i);
        }
        return pse;
    }

    private long sumSubarrayMaxs(int[] arr) {

        int[] pge = findPge(arr);
        int[] nge = findNge(arr);
        long total = 0;
        int mod = (int)(1e9 + 7);

        for(int i=0; i<arr.length; i++){
            int left = i - pge[i];
            int right = nge[i] - i;
            total += 1L * left * right * arr[i];
        }

        return total;
    }

    private int[] findNge(int[] arr){
        Deque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        int n = arr.length;
        int[] nge = new int[n];

        for(int i=n-1; i>=0; i--){
            //Why there is no = sign in while condition ?
            // Because of an edge case where elements are same say 1,1. In this case
            // the 1st index element 1 will duplicate a subarray that has already been calculated as a result 
            // to eliminate this edge case, we didn't use = sign
            while(!stack.isEmpty() && arr[stack.peek()] < arr[i]){
                stack.pop();
            }

            nge[i] = stack.isEmpty() ? n : stack.peek();
            stack.push(i);
        }
        return nge;
    }

    private int[] findPge(int[] arr){
        Deque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        int n = arr.length;
        int[] pge = new int[n];

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            
            while(!stack.isEmpty() && arr[stack.peek()] <= arr[i]){
                stack.pop();
            }

            pge[i] = stack.isEmpty() ? -1 : stack.peek();
            stack.push(i);
        }
        return pge;
    }


    public long subArrayRanges(int[] nums) {

        long result = sumSubarrayMaxs(nums) - sumSubarrayMins(nums);

        return result;
        
    }
}
